data.enText: a person who is the official head of a country or region that is governed by another country
the former governor of the colony
a person who is chosen to be in charge of the government of a state in the US

data.chText: （学校、学院、医院等机构的）董事，理事
data.enText: a member of a group of people who are responsible for controlling an institution such as a school, a college or a hospital
the board of governors of the college
a person who is in charge of an institution
the governor of the Bank of England

data.chText: 我作不了主，我得问问老板。
data.enText: I can't decide. I'll have to ask the governor (= the man in charge, who employs sb) .

simple_means.memory_skill: govern 统治，管理 + or 人 → 州长，地方长官

means: (学校、学院、医院等机构的)董事，理事

tr: a control that maintains a steady speed in a machine (as by controlling the supply of fuel)
the head of a state government

value.def: In some systems of government, a governor is a person who is in charge of the political administration of a region or state.

example.ex: He was governor of the province in the late 1970s...
example.tran: 他在20世纪70年代末担任该省的省长。

example.ex: Governor William Livingston addressed the New Jersey Assembly.
example.tran: 威廉·利文斯顿州长在新泽西州议会上发表了演说。

value.def: A governor is a member of a committee which controls an organization such as a school or a hospital.

example.ex: Governors are using the increased powers given to them to act against incompetent headteachers.
example.tran: 董事们运用赋予他们的更大权力罢免不称职的校长。

example.ex: ...the chairman of the BBC board of governors.
example.tran: 英国广播公司董事会主席

value.def: In some British institutions, the governor is the most senior official, who is in charge of the institution.

example.ex: The incident was reported to the prison governor.
example.tran: 这一事件已汇报给监狱长。

trans: 总督﹙派驻政治统辖国的官方代表，尤指英国国王或女王派驻英联邦国家的代表﹚
